POLOKWANE – Despite a windy start to the week, conditions are expected to clear in Polokwane from Wednesday (July 27). Clear skies and mild temperatures are forecast for this week with temperatures expected to peak in the low to mid twenties.  According to People’s Weather’s forecast, maximum temperatures will range from 18ºC to 24ºC and no rain has been forecast. The week will start off with partly cloudy conditions and cool temperatures with Monday reaching a high of 18ºC while Sunday (July 31) will be the warmest day of the week with maximum temperatures peaking at a warm 24ºC. Minimum temperatures will range between 8ºC and 11ºC. 